<md:title>Cloud top altitudes observed with airborne lidar during the ACLOUD campaign</md:title>
<md:source id="dataset.sourceinst33" >Alfred Wegener Institute - Research Unit Potsdam</md:source>
<md:URI>https://doi.org/10.1594/PANGAEA.899962</md:URI>
<md:dateTime>2019-04-03T08:43:28</md:dateTime>
</md:citation>
<md:abstract>During the ACLOUD (Arctic CLoud Observations Using airborne measurements during polar Day) campaign conducted in May / June 2017, the Airborne Mobile Aerosol Lidar (AMALi) was used to measure the cloud top altitude of clouds below the aircraft Polar 5. The data set provides cloud top altitude along the flight tracks of 14 flights performed by the Polar 5 aircraft in 5 Hz resolution.</md:abstract>
